# Anti-patterns (enforced for all scopes)

RULE: Do not write functions whose sole purpose is templating or generating
report prose as strings.
RULE: Do not write tests that assert on report text content, file existence,
or notebook source code.
RULE: Do not return arithmetic-identity DataFrames from `src/` functions
for the sole purpose of making them unit-testable.
RULE: Do not persist DataFrames to `data/processed/` if they are only used
for display in a notebook or report and have no downstream consumer.
RULE: Do not create orchestrator functions that return 10+ named outputs —
return only what a downstream step or the report actually uses.
